check_results.remediation:
Add all four mandatory tags to every CDK Construct.  Use cdk.Tags.of(scope) to apply tags at the stack level so they propagate to all child resources:
  cdk.Tags.of(this).add("cost-center", "my-team");
  cdk.Tags.of(this).add("owner", "my-team");
  cdk.Tags.of(this).add("environment", "prod");
  cdk.Tags.of(this).add("workload", "my-service");

Add lifecycle rules when constructing the Bucket:
  new s3.Bucket(this, "DataBucket", {
    lifecycleRules: [{
      transitions: [
        { storageClass: s3.StorageClass.INFREQUENT_ACCESS, transitionAfter: cdk.Duration.days(30) },
        { storageClass: s3.StorageClass.GLACIER,            transitionAfter: cdk.Duration.days(90) },
      ],
      expiration: cdk.Duration.days(2555),
    }],
  });

Set backupRetention to at least cdk.Duration.days(1):
  new rds.DatabaseInstance(this, "Db", {
    backupRetention: cdk.Duration.days(7),
  });

Add an image_scanning_configuration block to all aws_ecr_repository resources:
  image_scanning_configuration { scan_on_push = true }
For enhanced scanning, enable Amazon Inspector at the account level and configure continuous ECR scanning via aws_inspector2_enabler resource.

Set backupRetention when constructing the DatabaseInstance:
  new rds.DatabaseInstance(this, "Db", {
    backupRetention: cdk.Duration.days(14),
  });

Pass an explicit encryptionKey to the Bucket construct:
  const cmk = new kms.Key(this, "Cmk", { enableKeyRotation: true });
  new s3.Bucket(this, "DataBucket", { encryptionKey: cmk });

Set storageEncrypted: true and supply storageEncryptionKey when constructing the DatabaseInstance or DatabaseCluster:
  new rds.DatabaseInstance(this, "Db", {
    storageEncrypted: true,
    storageEncryptionKey: cmk,
  });
